fields.Title: JAM / HORSEBACK MONUMENT
fields.Description: On the traffic island in the jam, an old monument of Filippe III The Squanderer pointing towards an unknown location in the sea. The chest region seems to have suffered chip damage.

fields.Title: You: "What did this king do?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What did this king do?
fields.variable3: CheckEquipped("jacket_caribineer")  and  (CheckEquipped("boots_cavalry")  or  CheckEquipped("pants_caribineer")  or  CheckEquipped("neck_setting_sun_medal"))

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "High above you, the king stands tri..."
fields.Dialogue Text: High above you, the king stands triumphantly oblivious to your memory trouble.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "But wait! You haven't even heard ab..."
fields.Dialogue Text: But wait! You haven't even heard about his fabled cocaine addiction.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Neither do people in Martinaise. Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Neither do people in Martinaise. The statue has proved to be *controversial* in a neighbourhood mostly populated by the left-leaning working class.

fields.Title: You: "Who is this?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Who is this?

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Well... Martinaise is riddled with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well... Martinaise is riddled with bullet holes. This place saw a lot of action during the Revolution. But the statue *is* recently renovated -- so maybe a joke? Target practice? Or a political statement?"

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "We'll see."
fields.Dialogue Text: We'll see.

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "Filippe III, the Squanderer, howeve..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Filippe III, the Squanderer, however, with his bronze face up in the air, doesn't seem concerned about what the *hoi polloi* think of him in death.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "There's not an *ounce* of artistry..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's not an *ounce* of artistry here! It's even worse than expected.

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "An old monument stands in the middl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An old monument stands in the middle of the traffic island, pointing toward the sea. The horse and rider appear to be struggling against the vibrantly coloured cables and coiled wire.
fields.Alternate1: The old king and his horse appear to be struggling against the vibrantly coloured cables and coiled wire.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He takes a note. "I've made a note...."
fields.Dialogue Text: He takes a note. "I've made a note. Don't hold your breath."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Why not?" He shrugs. "What this sh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why not?" He shrugs. "What this shows us is guns aren't too uncommon here. And people still shoot them. Sometimes at kings." He takes a note in his notebook.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "His own maladministration foreshado..."
fields.Dialogue Text: His own maladministration foreshadowed the fall of the monarchy during the Antecentennial Revolution, an end to his family line and the monarchy on the Insulindian isola.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "That's what the revolutionaries sai..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's what the revolutionaries said -- 150 years later. Right before they emptied out the royal mausoleum and dumped His Majesty's mortal remains in the Insulindian Bay.

fields.Title: You: "Wait, really? There's no way that's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, really? There's no way that's true.

fields.Title: Authority: "This is slander. The king was just..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is slander. The king was just and beautiful. The revolutionaries made this all up.

fields.Title: You: "I *really* don't get art."
fields.Dialogue Text: I *really* don't get art.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: "In what way?"
fields.Dialogue Text: In what way?

fields.Title: Jump to: [Horseback Monument: "Filippe III's ludicrous bronze like..."]
Horrific Necktie: "The man certainly knew how to live!"
fields.Dialogue Text: The man certainly knew how to live!

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "The king stands high above you, sur..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The king stands high above you, surveying the bay. Mute and indifferent to your sightings.

fields.Title: You: "That's brilliant! So funny and nihi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's brilliant! So funny and nihilistic.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "People in Martinaise tend to agree,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: People in Martinaise tend to agree, as do many prominent art critics and thought leaders with more *nuanced* social awareness than the young ironists.

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "The roundabout is quiet, almost eer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so under the brilliant sun. The king of disco is lit up like a stage, anticipating a funky beat that will never come...
fields.Alternate1: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so under the sodium lights. The apricot sceptre illuminates the disco king like a beacon in the dark, calling all dancers to wait for the drop of the next funky beat...
fields.Alternate2: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so in the rain. Drops fall around the apricot sceptre and bounce off the glitter balls, yet the noble king of disco still hunts unperturbed for the next funky beat...
fields.Alternate3: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so in the snow. The apricot sceptre glows fiercer upon the white sheets, held up by the frozen king of disco who hunts for the next funky beat...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Looks like the students took your..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Looks like the students took your advice to heart, detective."

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "A silver plaque on the statue's ped..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A silver plaque on the statue's pedestal reads: 'I am Filippe III, the Squanderer, the Greatest of the Filippian Kings of Revachol; Son of Filippe II, the Opulent; Father of Filippe IV, the Insane.'
fields.Alternate1: Pulling aside the poster covering the statue's pedestal reveals: 'I am Filippe III, the Squanderer, the Greatest of the Filippian Kings of Revachol; Son of Filippe II, the Opulent; Father of Filippe IV, the Insane.'

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Okay..." He cleans his glasses bef..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay..." He cleans his glasses before looking up. "I can't see it. But I'll take your word for it."

fields.Title: You: "The king is the king and he can do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The king is the king and he can do *anything*.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Most historians think the Coalition..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Most historians think the Coalition's hasty landing may have ultimately *saved* the statue: If the communards had more time they would have reduced it up to even *finer* pieces.

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "At the bottom of the posters, in sm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: At the bottom of the posters, in smaller lettering, are details about meeting at a local coffeehouse.

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "An old monument stands in the middl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An old monument stands in the middle of the traffic island, pointing toward the sea. The whole thing is wrapped in vibrantly coloured cables and coiled wire. Where the horse's head should be, only twisted pieces of rebar remain.
fields.Alternate1: The old monument is wrapped in vibrantly coloured cables and coiled wire. Where the horse's head should be, only twisted pieces of rebar remain.

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "There are no lights that spell out..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There are no lights that spell out your name, no workers with calloused hands leering from above -- just construction materials displayed as if to mourn your misplaced dreams.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Some years ago a group of liberal,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Some years ago a group of liberal, artistically inclined individuals (designers mostly) thought it would be *ironic* to restore the statue of the most wasteful ruler of Revachol in the poorest part of the city...

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Not that he ever did in life, eithe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not that he ever did in life, either.

fields.Title: You: "Examine the scaffolding."
fields.Dialogue Text: Examine the scaffolding.

fields.Title: You: "Okay. Where is he buried now? (Proc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Okay. Where is he buried now? (Proceed.)

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "An old monument stands in the middl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An old monument stands in the middle of the traffic island. It is surrounded by scaffolding that has been haphazardly erected around it.
fields.Alternate1: An old monument stands in the middle of the traffic island. It is surrounded by scaffolding that has been haphazardly erected around it.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "His Majesty's courtiers said it hel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: His Majesty's courtiers said it helped him connect with the *Higher Realms*.

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "Not just *any* nose candy, though...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not just *any* nose candy, though. We're talking royal *Filippian* blow, allegedly twice as potent as the stuff you find nowadays. And purple, Filippian cocaine was purple.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "The original was blown apart by com..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The original was blown apart by communards, then further damaged during the landing of the Coalition's airships during the Turn-Of-The-Century Revolution. When Martinaise was levelled.

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "The roundabout is quiet, almost eer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so under the brilliant sunlight. The doom crier in the centre waits to be swallowed by the bright sky, his cardboard omen flapping in the wind like live bait...
fields.Alternate1: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so under the sodium lights. The doom crier embraces the blackened sky, his cardboard omen hiding its ill fortune in the dark...
fields.Alternate2: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so in the rain. The doom crier welcomes the wet erosion, his cardboard omen starting to sag under the weight of the weather...
fields.Alternate3: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so in the snow. The doom crier embraces the deathly cold, his cardboard omen dusted with what looks like sky-fallen ash...

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "The roundabout is quiet, almost eer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so under the brilliant sunlight. The formless complexion glows at the centre, while the old architecture surrounding it groans in the heat with looming irrelevance...
fields.Alternate1: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so under the sodium lights. The formless complexion glows at the centre, each street lamp failing to replicate the shining brilliance of its rebellion...
fields.Alternate2: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so in the rain. The painted surface at the centre welcomes the droplets like a water slide. Around it, the coast's older architecture enjoys nothing but slow erosion...
fields.Alternate3: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so in the snow. The paint is a runny yolk at the centre, the birth cell of a new style -- ready to be dipped into and nourish the youth with sticky inspiration...

fields.Title: You: ""Lieutenant -- has someone *shot* t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Lieutenant -- has someone *shot* the king?" (Point to the indentation)

fields.Title: You: "Don't mention it."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't mention it.

fields.Title: You: "So he was addicted to nose candy. A..."
fields.Dialogue Text: So he was addicted to nose candy. A bloated druggie?

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "Something with great kinetic energy..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something with great kinetic energy seems to have impacted the cuirass... around where the 'heart' is. A bullet?

fields.Title: You: ""What do you think?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you think?"

fields.Title: Shivers: "A group of marble pleurants still s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A group of marble pleurants still surrounds the king's vandalized tomb... A deathly cold wind sweeps up candy wrappers and old newspapers.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "You see, Old Filippe wasn't just go..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You see, Old Filippe wasn't just good at squandering the national treasury on gold and ceremonial weaponry. He was also a prodigious snorter of nose candy.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Cocaine."
fields.Dialogue Text: Cocaine.

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "The scaffolding around the old monu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The scaffolding around the old monument has been taken down. In its place are the spoils of your investment. Numerous rods and ropes still hold the original reassemblage in place.

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "The old king looks defiantly to the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The old king looks defiantly to the west, wrapped in makeshift scaffolding like a mummy...

fields.Title: You: ""None of the above. Maybe it's conn..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "None of the above. Maybe it's connected to the murder?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""If we connect every bullet hole in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If we connect every bullet hole in Martinaise to the murder, we'll get an overwhelming amount of loose threads..." He takes his notebook out. "But then again, our guy *was* shot. And that hole would be recent."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Stories have it that he had his bed..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Stories have it that he had his bedroom converted into a treasure chamber where he stored unfathomable wealth: *krugerrands*, bars of gold, ornate weaponry, armour, and various chalices.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "He called it the *Sol Aurum*. It wa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He called it the *Sol Aurum*. It was obscene. There were whispers he slept on a huge pile of gold-dipped feathers like some obese dragon, instead of a bed like a normal person.

fields.Title: You: "A deplorable farce. No wonder every..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A deplorable farce. No wonder everything went to shit.

fields.Title: You: "That's such a bad idea."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's such a bad idea.

fields.Title: You: "Who restored the monument?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Who restored the monument?

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "A matrix of metal tubes and wooden..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A matrix of metal tubes and wooden planks jut out at odd angles. A miserable tarpaulin covers up the horse and rider, flapping in the cold coastal air...

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "An old monument stands in the middl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An old monument stands in the middle of the traffic island, pointing toward the sea. It's been covered in posters with radical slogans like 'NO KINGS, NO BOSSES' and 'AGAIN, AND ONCE MORE AFTER THAT!'
fields.Alternate1: The old king and his horse have been covered in posters with radical slogans like 'NO KINGS, NO BOSSES' and 'AGAIN, AND ONCE MORE AFTER THAT!'¬†

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Someone's shot him in the heart. In..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Someone's shot him in the heart. Interesting.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "The more you ask yourself, the less..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The more you ask yourself, the less you know. One thing is for certain, though: you're brain-damaged. It's serious. And permanent.

fields.Title: You: "I don't want to know."
fields.Dialogue Text: I don't want to know.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "This is *not* what that Personal Br..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is *not* what that Personal Brand Strategist of yours promised. No one even knows that you're paying for this re-conceptualization! Go and have a word with him. Find out what's going on.

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "An old monument stands in the middl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An old monument stands in the middle of the traffic island, pointing toward the sea. It looks as if it's been reassembled piece-by-piece, secured and mounted in the air with the aid of numerous ropes and rods.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Horseback Monument: "The king stands high above you, sur..."]
You: "Fair enough, I have other questions..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Fair enough, I have other questions. (Stop the knowledge from pouring in.)

fields.Title: You: "The what now?"
fields.Dialogue Text: The what now?

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "The statue is supposed to capture t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The statue is supposed to capture the moment it was blown apart, like *an instant frozen in time*. A rare butterfly, trapped in amber, floating on a sea of... shit.

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "The roundabout is quiet, almost eer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so under the brilliant sunlight. The penumbral griever is a silhouette against the bright sky, the flowers lifting him in requiem starting to wilt...
fields.Alternate1: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so under the sodium lights. Darkness completely engulfs the penumbral griever, the flowers lifting him in requiem starting to wilt...
fields.Alternate2: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so in the rain. Drops fall like tears down the veil of the penumbral griever, while a few fallen petals drift like funerary boats downstream, weeping into drains...
fields.Alternate3: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so in the snow. The penumbral griever cuts black its misery against the white weather, the flowers lifting him in requiem starting to wilt in the cold...

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "The monument stands high above you...."
fields.Dialogue Text: The monument stands high above you. Mute and indifferent to your sightings.

fields.Title: You: ""Mhm, target practice.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mhm, target practice."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He takes a note. "It's not *complet..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He takes a note. "It's not *completely* tangential -- at least worth noting down. I wouldn't hold my breath, though."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""If we connect every bullet hole in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If we connect every bullet hole in Martinaise to the murder, we'll get an overwhelming amount of loose threads..." He takes his notebook out. "But then again, we don't really know what we're dealing with here, so..."

fields.Title: You: "This is... a lot to process."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is... a lot to process.

fields.Title: You: "I would like to sleep on gold. Hust..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I would like to sleep on gold. Hustler-style.

fields.Title: You: "What indentations? What do I see?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What indentations? What do I see?

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Well, he blew through the whole nat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Well, he blew through the whole national treasury, starting the decline of one of the penultimate century's greatest superpowers: the Suzerain of Revachol...

fields.Title: You: "How did he manage to blow through *..."
fields.Dialogue Text: How did he manage to blow through *the entire national treasury*?

fields.Title: You: "Reflect on the re-conceptualization..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Reflect on the re-conceptualization.

dialogueEntries.conditionsString: Variable["TASK.report_to_the_tribunal_done"]  and  (Variable["plaza.ultralib_monument_apocalypse"]  or  Variable["plaza.ultralib_monument_superstar"]  or  Variable["plaza.ultralib_monument_sorry"]  or  Variable["plaza.ultralib_monument_boring"]  or  Variable["plaza.ultralib_monument_art"])

fields.Title: You: ""Political. It's a *king* and he's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Political. It's a *king* and he's shot."

fields.Title: Half Light: "That son of a bitch scammed you! Pr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That son of a bitch scammed you! Probably to *make fun of you*...

fields.Title: You: ""Yes, a practical joke.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, a practical joke."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "People in Martinaise tend to disagr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: People in Martinaise tend to disagree, as do many prominent art critics and thought leaders with more *nuanced* social awareness than the young ironists.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "As you look up, you notice somethin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As you look up, you notice something about the statue. There are some odd indentations on the king's chest piece...

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "The roundabout is quiet, almost eer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so under the brilliant sunlight. The tickets remain true to their duty -- except for a few that have come unstuck, now assigned to brushing dirt from the asphalt below...
fields.Alternate1: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so under the sodium lights. The tickets remain true to their duty, ready for the night shift -- except for a few that have come unstuck, now assigned to brushing dirt from the asphalt below...
fields.Alternate2: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so in the rain. The sodden tickets remain true to their duty against the storm -- except for a few that lie face down below, honourably drowned in a puddle...
fields.Alternate3: The roundabout is quiet, almost eerily so in the snow. The tickets remain true to their duty, like a crowd of commuters huddled for warmth -- except for a few that have come unstuck, now assigned to raking the drifts below...

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Those critics might have it wrong,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Those critics might have it wrong, though. There's more to it than just 'ironism'... but you can't say what precisely. Perhaps this art mystery will be solved at a later time?

fields.Title: Volition: "Not a good track record of mental h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not a good track record of mental health in that family.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Even by the standards of the Filipp..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Even by the standards of the Filippian kings, Old Sumptuous Filippe was known for his profligacy.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Beneath the cold waters of the Insu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Beneath the cold waters of the Insulindian Bay, thrown there by the revolutionaries after they cleaned out the royal mausoleum.

fields.Title: Horseback Monument: "Filippe III's ludicrous bronze like..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Filippe III's ludicrous bronze likeness looks defiantly up into the sky.

fields.Title: You: "Okay, what is nose candy?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Okay, what is nose candy?

fields.Title: You: "What happened to the statue?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What happened to the statue?

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "What did he do? You have no idea wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What did he do? You have no idea what *you* did a week ago! How would you know what this guy did many centuries ago?
